        "Exclusive Shelf": "read",
        "My Review": "(don’t necessarily rate memoirs and the 4 stars is not a reflection of how much i enjoyed the memoir but moreso an admiration for sharing her story & taking her power back)<br/><br/>to read about everything in this book made my skin crawl - there is only so much a human can tolerate in their lifetime, and these kids have tolerated and seen so much more than kids should ever have to see. this book serves as a good reminder in times like these about the dangers of commodifying your child’s life where we are seeing products of family vlogging finally turn into adults who can talk about their story.<br/><br/>Parents vying to be influencers need to do a better job of protecting their kids and not using farming their kids lives for content. The story of 8Passengers goes further beyond that tho; Ruby Franke is a product of her childhood & unresolved trauma further amplified by her life partner who chose to stay blind to everything that was happening and Jodi, who aided in the absolute destruction of the family in guise of therapy.<br/><br/>It is almost terrifying to see the levels to which Ruby was already exhibiting science of physical abuse alongside emotional even when her eldest were at a young age and the worst part is that reading excerpts from when Ruby was a YouTuber, despite not having seen their content before, as a normal viewer, I bet I could not have even figured that something was amis, with what Ruby was saying re her parenting ideologies which makes it worse because child abuse becomes that much harder to detect.<br/><br/><br/>Reading parts where Jodi was introduced was especially painful seeing the level of gaslighting, and self doubt  that she was integrating into the lives of everyone who were in vulnerable positions looking to better themselves and trusted her with their feelings. The part where Shari speaks about how Jodi is truly masterful at what she does; how we think we would he immune to it until we actually encounter about is a tale in caution about not letting yourself fall into an echo chamber to protect yourself from cults especially those guised under wellness.<br/><br/><br/>To end with, I hope that the author and all the kids involved are able to process the lifetime trauma and move forward untangling the deeply ingrained thought process of denigration from their mindset. I hope the author is also able to recognise the role their own echo chamber of a community played in perpetuating the beliefs that ultimately turned on this family.<br/><br/>Ultimately, this is a commentary on how our system continues to fail us - How can multiple reports to the CPS go unnoticed and be dismissed due to the lack of evidence? Child abuse is not always visible and the system needs to do a better job of protecting children who are the most vulnerable to abuse under the hands of their parents.",
