        "Exclusive Shelf": "read",
        "My Review": "You know the feeling when the book you're reading engulfs you in a warm hug,makes you a part of its world and every character feels like an old friend you know? This was that book for me.<br/>\"A Good Girl's Guide to Murder\" felt like home.With the old town setting & the sneaking around Pippa did, I was bombarded with memories of being a young kid and reading Famous Five/Nancy Drew.  <br/><br/>Initially,I felt myself grumbling about the details given to the monotony of her life after every production log but as I read,I came to really appreciate the focus given to building Pippa's life beyond just the mystery. I've come to expect every character to have a life so intricate and complex because of the books I've read aimed as dark mystery however, this was an eye-opener to the fact that most young adults (such as myself) have had sheltered lives that revolve around books,universities and perhaps the occasional murder-mystery EPQ.<br/><br/>I loved the breakdown of this perfect little town into a town clouded with well-kept secrets lurking under the surface . Most characters,for me,were in the grey zone hanging between the right and the wrong due to their actions,motives and ultimately,the chain reaction that their actions started off.<br/><br/>The use of mixed media made the book highly interactive and I found myself constantly connecting different suspects for the likelihood of our <spoiler>double murder duo </spoiler><br/><br/>If I had to pick,I'd take the speech Pippa gives in the very last chapter as the perfect end to a tumultuous ride.It highlighted so many things - not only about the victim but also of those involved - in the sense that most cases shell out everyone as one-dimensional but there are so many layers to each of them and I am happy that it was explored bit-by-bit as it was in this book and not all at once. The revelation bought on by all the pieces clicking at the very end was the cherry.<br/>To be honest,I've just finished the book and I expect to write a better review but as of now,my heart is just so full that I finally read a book that got me clapping and screaming at my screen. <br/>P.S - I just saw it's set to be a series so now I know what is going to be my next buy.",
