        "My Review": "5 stars because not only did I finish it in one sitting but I am sitting wide awake at 4:30am marveling at this thriller.<br/><br/><br/>All The Dangerous Things follows all the typical makings of a thriller - an unreliable narrator, a stranger looking to solve the case, a mystery in her past and a fractured family in the present but Stacy Willingham does something truly marvelous with all these cliché elements - she creates a story so distinctly her own. It could be my own disillusionment speaking at the feeling of finally ripping through a book in one sitting but to be able to constantly keep the reader interested even when the twists are obvious is a feat all on its own. The pacing and structure of this book is incredible - all the twists come at the right spots, the reveals are clever and the foreshadowing brilliant. The book is fast, happening over the span of a few days, keeping me on my toes constantly and it gets right the one thing a lot of thrillers don't: flashbacks. The flashbacks in this book were sprinkled in throughout the narrative revealing the story little by little which was perfect. <br/><br/>The <i> then </i> part was giving me haunting of bly manor and that's all the push i can give you to read the book! The <now> does such an unexpected reveal on the biggest true crime cliché (100 points if you get it) - I had the killer pegged 1 hour in but the road to get there was so good, it was worth it.",
