        "My Review": "edit - 3.5 stars, rounded down. Goodreads, let us do half-star ratings, please?<br/><br/>I've just finished this book and the rating has gone through a tumultuous decline going from 5 stars to 3 stars because the more I dwell on it, the more problems I have with it narratively. Now I am fully aware of how most of the problems with Scarlet are just pet peeves of my own in fantasies but it is what it is. <br/><br/><b> 1. Character Development </b> - While Cinder served to be a good insight into Cinder's personality since her emotions were at the forefront of the book, I feel that by the end of it, I had a pretty good idea of who Cinder was and I was rooting for her. However, in Scarlet, I feel that you don't learn a LOT about Scarlet. The struggle to find her grandmother starts as a pivotal problem for her but that only holds for the first 10 chapters, after which we are treated to 20 chapters of Scar and Wolf's budding romance (with no indication of why they are attracted to each other beyond the fact that they are main characters). I came out of this book, feeling that Scarlet was only a caricature of a person and her main role was to depend on someone and have them be the reason for her entire emotional growth, be it her grandmother or Wolf lol <br/><br/><b> 2. Romance </b> - I find the romance cringy. Idk what to tell you but her trusting him immediately made no sense given the person we'd been shown so far (hence tying into the lack of Scar's character development since she goes against everything she stands for in the first 5 chapters itself). Wolf gives her reasons to not trust him again and again but she does just because?? Sorry but that was incredibly ungrounded and honestly, the conflict between them lasts for a day virtually, in the span of which he kisses her to help rescue her while she is evidently emotionally taxed but yay he's the hero, I guess?? and then the conflict is solved by 'he's not like the rest of them' - why? he just likes you and so he's not like the rest of them. stfu. For once, I wish they had an actual conversation about how his betrayal actually hurt her instead of letting bygones be bygones because yum big sexy dog <3 <br/><br/><b> 3. Just more complaints </b> -  This entire book was giving me ✨Wattpad Werewolf Romances✨ and I feel like a lot of phrases such as <i> This one is mine! </i> which only contributes to treating women as objects were used with the excuse of primal instincts and honestly was really underwhelming.<br/><br/><b> The Saving Graces </b> - Thorne, ofc. He was giving me Flynn Rider from Tangled the entire time and I feel his character is just the right mix of comedy relief and a person who comes through in difficult times. Iko - I love their personality so much and I just wanted more scenes of their interaction with Thorne. Cinder - she's very good with strategy and she was much smarter in this book, left to her own devices.",
